TWS / IB Gateway Settings

For paper trading, open TWS or IB Gateway and enable API access.

Suggested paper ports:

TWS Paper: 7497
TWS Live: 7496
IB Gateway Paper: 4002

In TWS:

Go to Edit → Global Configuration → API → Settings
Enable:
Enable ActiveX and Socket Clients
Allow connections from localhost only
Set the correct socket port
Turn Read-Only API off if you want order placement enabled
Configuration

Main settings are in config.py.

Important sections:

IBKRConfig → broker connection settings
TimeConfig → trading windows and timezone
IndicatorConfig → symbol, bar size, indicator periods
OptionsConfig → option type, moneyness, premium cap
RiskConfig → stop loss, daily loss, max trades
AIConfig → Claude model and prompt instructions
BotConfig → top-level configuration and paper/live mode
Running the Bot

Start TWS or IB Gateway first, then run:

python bot.py

The bot will:

Connect to Interactive Brokers
Pull recent QQQ bars
Compute indicators
Generate a setup signal
Evaluate the setup using:
Claude, if configured
rule-based logic otherwise
Pass the trade through risk checks
Submit an order if all checks pass
Sleep and repeat on the configured loop interval
